        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 23 at 3:18PM MDT by NWS Cheyenne WY</headline>
        <description>At 318 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Meriden Rest Area, or 36 miles south of Torrington, moving east at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
La Grange and Meriden Rest Area.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM MDT for
the Panhandle of Nebraska...and southeastern Wyoming.</instruction>
